cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper deals with sentiment analysis of text, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of visualizations to track emotions, which falls under the category of data visualization and could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of crowdsourcing to create a word-emotion association lexicon is a machine learning technique, which could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses gender differences in the use of emotion words, which could be classified under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
